gomodel:SYNGO_4699  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1: Pum2 negatively regulates dendritic outgrowth. Loss of Pum2 leads to enhanced dendritic arborization, and overexpression of Pum2 causes the reverse effect.\n\nFigure 2: Pum2 regulates dendritic spine morphology and mEPSC frequency.\n\nFigure 3: Pum2 regulates excitatory synapse numbers.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Rat hippocampal neurons were cultured and transiently transfected as described\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
